Name: SMF30INP
Description: Number of card-image records in DD DATA and DD* data sets read by the reader for the map. This field is not set for subtypes 2 or 3.

Name: SMF30TEP
Description: Total blocks transferred (accumulated execute channel program (EXCP) counts - valid up to X'FFFFFFFE', zero and invalid when SMF30TEF is set)

Name: SMF30TPT
Description: Number of TPUTS (terminal writes) for a TSO/E session. If a batch job or a started task successfully processes TPUTs, this field might be non-zero for batch jobs or started tasks.

Name: SMF30TGT
Description: Number of TGETS (terminal reads) for a TSO/E session.

Name: SMF30RDR
Description: Reader device class as defined in JESPARMS. 0 — for TSO/E sessions or started tasks.

Name: SMF30RDT
Description: Reader device type as defined in JESPARMS. 0 — for TSO/E sessions or started tasks.

Name: SMF30TCN
Description: Total device connect time (in 128 micro-second units) for this address space. For a DIV object, this field contains total device connect time for reads, writes, and re-reads.

Name: SMF30DCF
Description: Flag word

Name: SMF30RSB
Description: Reserved.

Name: SMF30TRR
Description: Total address space REREAD count.

Name: SMF30AIC
Description: DASD I/O connect time, in 128-microsecond units, for address space plus dependent enclaves. Note that the value of RqsvAIC for FICON® channel utilization cannot be calculated. For more information, see the footnote.

Name: SMF30AID
Description: DASD I/O disconnect time, in 128-microsecond units, for address space plus dependent enclaves.

Name: SMF30AIW
Description: DASD I/O pending plus control unit queue time, in 128-microsecond units, for address space plus dependent enclaves.

Name: SMF30AIS
Description: DASD I/O start subchannel count for address space plus dependent enclaves.

Name: SMF30EIC
Description: DASD I/O connect time, in 128-microsecond units, for independent enclaves owned by the address space. Note that the value of RqsvEIC for FICON channel utilization cannot be calculated. For more information, see the footnote.

Name: SMF30EID
Description: DASD I/O disconnect time, in 128-microsecond units, for independent enclaves owned by the address space.

Name: SMF30EIW
Description: DASD I/O pending plus control unit queue time, in 128-microsecond units, for independent enclaves owned by the address space.

Name: SMF30EIS
Description: DASD I/O start subchannel count for independent enclaves.

Name: SMF30TEX
Description: Total blocks transferred - accumulated EXCP counts. This field is the 8-byte equivalent of SMF30TEP, but this field remains valid after SMF30TEP is invalid.

Name: SMF30DAS
Description: Number of DDs that had their DD accounting information suppressed.
